title: VIOLENT: Students smashing windows, London protest over tuition fees at 30 Millbank
description: A huge protest against the British government's plan to triple university tuition fees descended into violence today after hundreds of angry demonstrators smashed their way into the London headquarters of Prime Minister David Cameron's Conservative Party.    The scale of the London protest defied expectations, with an estimated 50,000 turning out to vent their anger at government plans to raise tuition fees while cutting the state grant for university teaching.    Britain's most senior police officer was tonight forced to admit he was "embarrassed" that his officers had lost control of the capital's streets in scenes reminiscent of last year's G20 demonstration.    The mayor of London, Boris Johnson, said police should ask how a small minority of students had "shamefully abused their right to protest".

Asimismo, los precios al productor y al consumidor concentrarán parte de la atención. title: Lisbon Revisited
description: Não: não quero nada. Já disse que não quero nada.  Não me venham com conclusões! A única conclusão é morrer.  Não me tragam estéticas! Não me falem em moral! Tirem-me daqui a metafisica! Não me apregoem sistemas completos, não me enfileirem conquistas Das ciências (das ciências, Deus meu, das ciências!) ­ Das ciências, das artes, da civilização moderna!  Que mal fiz eu aos deuses todos?  Se têm a verdade, guardem-na!  Sou um técnico, mas tenho técnica só dentro da técnica. Fora disso sou doido, com todo o direito a sê-lo. Com todo o direito a sê-lo, ouviram?  Não me macem, por amor de Deus!  Queriam-me casado, fútil, quotidiano e tributável? Queriam-me o contrário disto, o contrário de qualquer coisa? Se eu fosse outra pessoa, fazia-lhes, a todos, a vontade. Assim, como sou, tenham paciência! Vão para o diabo sem mim, Ou deixem-me ir sozinho para o diabo! Para que havemos de ir juntos?  Não me peguem no braço! Não gosto que me peguem no braço. Quero ser sozinho. Já disse que sou sozinho! Ah, que maçada quererem que eu seja de companhia!  Ó céu azul ­ o mesmo da minha infância ­, Eterna verdade vazia e perfeita! Ó macio Tejo ancestral e mudo, Pequena verdade onde o céu se reflecte!  Ó mágoa revisitada, Lisboa de outrora de hoje! Nada me dais, nada me tirais, nada sois que eu me sinta. Deixem-me em paz! Não tardo, que eu nunca tardo... E enquanto tarda o Abismo e o Silêncio quero estar sozinho!

title: My miracle baby
description: My son Braylon was almost 2 years old when he started running a fever. We took him to the ER and they sent us home. Then we took him to the dr's office and they scheduled us an appointment for the next day because his blood count was high, The next day the dr noticed his groin area was swollen and suspected a hernia and possible bowel obstruction. We rushed to the closest children's hospital for surgery. You can imagine our shock when the surgeon came out after surgery and informed us that his appendix had ruptured over a week prior to the operation. It was a miracle that he survived. He never even showed signs of being in pain. They then informed us that he had a rare condition called Amyand's hernia that caused his appendix to rupture and the infection created the hernia. This condition only happens 0.1% in children. He is the 31st child to have his operation and condition documented. We were released with a PICC line. This is a catheter/ iv inserted into a major artery in his heart. We gave him antibiotics at home for 2 uneventful weeks. When the PICC line was removed, the fever came back. His blood count was 40,000! We were admitted to another hospital closer to home. He had developed sepsis. The infection was in his blood stream. Praise God he made it to his 2nd Birthday!

title: 口角起爭執 男持槍射擊女頭部－民視新聞
description: 【民視即時新聞】新北市中和區今天凌晨發生一起疑似情殺的槍擊案，28歲陳姓女子，疑似與30歲的男友發生爭執，遭到男友持槍射擊頭部，危在旦夕，男子則趁隙逃逸，陳女的妹妹再發間聽到槍響後，發現姊姊到臥血泊，緊急報警送醫，但情況相當不樂觀。
hashtags: FTVN, FTV, 民視新聞, 民視, 社會, FTV News
transcript: 發生在今天的零誠新北市中和發生了一起14情殺的槍擊艾1名28歲女子一四跟三歲男友發生真職竟然遭到男友持槍涉及投部命在擔係而男友則是趁亂拖逃女子妹妹在聽到槍想之後發現姐姐是倒臥在雪波緊急的感情報警鬆一但現在情況相當不樂館向極暗 現場桌椅 相當靈亂看得出有正朝的痕跡上者的妹妹 難過到椅度 坦軟必須有有人參服記憶28歲的成績女子與男性有人以私發生感情糾紛在口角之後男子失控分而持槍朝女子的頭部開了兩槍成女髒場失去意識有生命的危險男子則馬上逃遺成女的妹妹在房內聽到槍相後發現解決重蛋 感情暴景鬆異全案的事發原因警方還在調查當中並呼籲開槍的男子出面頭案以理警案情明時新聞綜合報導

title: Cutting Reptile Claws
description: How to cut their claws safely. My rescued iguanas help me show you how to take care of reptile claws. You can sponsor them and help our non-profit work to help iguanas and educate more owners at www.petfinder.com/NC298.html
hashtags: green, health, binty, cut, iguana, claws, reptile
transcript: Cutting the Guana claws. I had a lot of requests for a video like this, so here it is. Now you want to start with your Guana or your reptile in a good mood on a day when they don't mind you messing with them. And you can see Gizmo here. She's allowing me to cut her claws. Now most reptiles don't like you to mess with their feet or their toes. But if you're careful, they'll let you do it. Now, I'm starting out with a brand new set of clippers. I use human clippers Just because that's what I'm used to, but you can use animal clippers or there's new type of Tools that grind down the edge of a fingernail But as you can see here, Gizmo is kind of pulling away a little bit after doing a few of them and that's fine You want to just give them a minute to relax and give them a little do-lapse scratch or something and then come back and start on the other side. And you want to start off inspecting the toes and claws. Make sure everything is fine and that it's all clean and there's no damage and see which one of the claws are still sharp so you'll know which ones to cut. And since see I circled the blood vessels in the nail you do not want to cut into this part because it will hurt very much they will bleed and they will not be very happy with you and they will not want you to cut their claws again anytime soon. Now if you do accidentally cut into this you can dip their toe nail into either some quick stop or cornstarch to make the bleeding stop right away and you want to do that because they don't have that much blood in their system anyway and then over the next day or two you want to make sure that they're kept very clean and they don't step into any of their own waste, which could get that fingernail infected. Now you want to cut right here where the dotted line is and you can see it's just below the quick where the blood is but yet it takes the tip off but you want to cut in the angle of the underside of the cloth so that they can still hook and grab onto things to pull themselves up but there's no tip to dig in to your skin and cut it and this is what it looks like like when it's done right. I can see I took my time and I didn't cut too far back so I didn't hurt her so she's nice and happy about that. You can see that she can still hook her claws onto things so she can pull herself up but she can't dig into them. So it's a happy day for her. She gets to go out on her branch for being a good girl and I'm happy because it's a lot easier on my skin. Now we'll see how I cut woody's claws my big wild male and usually I get him on the floor so that he can't fall off of anything, Casey spends around on me and I cover him with a towel so that he can't see my fingers to grab with his mouth and just to calm him down relax him he can bite into the towel if he wants. Now I inspect his toes and feet and of course he doesn't like this too much but he allows me to do it as long as I stay with cutting the very tips of his claws and don't get into the quick where it's going to hurt. Now after I get down with the back legs I move on to the front legs which he especially does not like me grabbing but as long as I go slow he'll let me pull those those out from under him and we'll get him out here. I inspect all of his toes and his claws make sure there's no damage anywhere and everything looks good. And the sooner you can cut these claws the better, it's less stressed on them and you have less of a chance of getting hurt while you're doing it. And if you just get really good at it, you can go one, two, three, get it done. And as soon as you get those claws done, you can see also that I'm cutting them at the same angle as the underneath part of their claws so that they can still hook on to things with the big part of the claw, just there won't be any tips to dig into your skin. Now after you get them done you back off a little bit and you slowly take the towel off and you can watch whoop and he spun around trying to get me and you can see he's a little disoriented but he's ready to go back in his room and he's done. Now because he was a good boy and he let me do that didn't put up a big fight then he gets a treat gets to go outside and son and enjoy himself for the rest of the day. So I hope you learned something and to those of you who requested a clock cutting video, I hope this helps you. Thanks so much!

description: PLEASE, READ THE DESCRIPTION/ POR FAVOR, LEAN LA DESCRIPCIÓN:    It was just a school project where we had to choose﻿ a story and tell it through photos. Some chose "Cinderella," we chose this, it seemed more fun to do. If we had wanted to do something seriously, we would have done the cosplay.    Este video lo hicieron unos amigos para un trabajo escolar de diseño grafico, donde se debia elegir un cuento; sacando fotografias a los miembros del grupo, representando los personajes, despues editar las fotos.    Los integrantes eligieron la cancion "Alice human sacrifice", una cancion de vocaloid cantada por Miku, Kaito, Meiko, Rin & Len.    Para hacerlo hubo bastante problemas XD, incluyendo que no se podian bajar los programas, ni poner los subtitulados, ademas que lo hicieron con la fecha limite de entrega u.u pero salio bien a mi parecer, como trabajo experimental, a mi me dieron ganas de hacer los otros videos (como la saga evil) XD siempre y cuando aprendamos a usar el sony vegas...                NOTA: porque la primera alice tenia un ojo sharingan? XD XD  eso nunca se supo....      NOTA 2: si, ya sabemos que la imagen del principio quedo colgada mucho tiempo...y que los subtitulos pasan muy rapido...pero fueron hecho a mano y pegados en cada foto XD pero bue

title: Houdini's Rope
description: http://www.galaxymagic.com        HOUDINI'S ROPE A Modern Classic Created by Jim Steinmeyer And produced in conjunction with Mak Magic  An astonishing one-man illusion, Houdini's Rope fills the stage with action and mystery; it's the perfect small illusion, a practical effect for almost any show.  Jim Steinmeyer's popular effect involves a hank of rope — supposedly an artifact from one of Houdini's famous escapes. "Many people thought that he could actually dematerialize and pass through the rope. It sounds incredible, but I'd like to give you a demonstration."  The magician stretches the rope across the stage and has it examined by two men from the audience. The spectators hold the ends of the rope as a small upright stand is rolled to the center of the rope. "This is the spot where I'm going to try to pass through the rope." The magician steps up onto the stand, framed by the wooden uprights. He pauses behind the taut rope, then covers the center of the rope with a square of cloth. Dramatically, he steps forward, until the audience can see that he's passed completely through Houdini's Rope!  Houdini's Rope is not only a perfect "first illusion," but an entertaining, mystifying routine for experienced illusionists. Mak Magic has developed a beautiful, practical prop for magicians, finished with natural wood and mounted on casters. You'll marvel at how efficiently it works.  The stand breaks down for packing and is small enough to use on almost any platform or stage, but the effect is large enough to be seen by any audience. The effect comes with Jim Steinmeyer's presentation from his book, Device and Illusion.

title: Syracuse Men's Rowing
transcript: The Syracuse men's and women's rowing teams practice in a simulated rowing boat to stay in shape over the winter. On day through Saturday, team of 40 men row between 7 and 9 miles of water tank over 100 years old. This tank is tucked away in the corner of the northern entrance to the archipel building on Syracuse campus. Just like in the races, the boat fits 8 men at a time. So rowers rotate and working on rowing machines or herbs and plights in addition to the boat. This training facility keeps the team in shape once winter hits. Lake Freeze is over. So we have to row inside to keep up with other schools. And we'll spend all winter inside on the tank and in the yards and we're just working on our fitness levels and trying to be as competitive as possible fitness wise. And then we work on our technique once we get back out on the water and the spring. For head coach Dave Reichman and his team, his transition occurs at Thanksgiving. The tank does get the lowers ready for spring, but it can still be a drag practicing inside. The real joy does come from being on water with the boat and making it go well and making it move smoothly. So it's really not something you look forward to training indoors, but it's something that's necessary to do. Although it may not be the same as being outside on the lake in a real boat, the inside tank and the rolling machines allows the Syracuse team to keep pace with those other teams that practice outside year round. title: Día de luto en Cataluña por la muerte de 4 bomberos en un incendio forestal  .
description: Horta de Sant Joan (Tarragona), 22 jul (EFE).-       Un total de 80 dotaciones de bomberos han trabajado toda la noche para estabilizar el perímetro del incendio que afecta al parque natural de Els Ports, en el término municipal de Horta de Sant Joan (Tarragona), y que ayer causó la muerte a cuatro bomberos y quemaduras graves a otros dos.      Fuentes de los bomberos de la Generalitat han informado a EFE de que el incendio, que se inició el lunes por la noche, todavía no se ha dado por controlado y que esta mañana se incrementarán los efectivos.      Respecto al estado de salud de los dos bomberos que resultaron heridos por un cambio súbito de la dirección del fuego, siguen en estado grave en la unidad de quemados del Valle Hebrón, y se está a la espera de que esta mañana se emita un nuevo parte médico.             Palabras clave: efe-incendio-forestal-tarragona
transcript: en Cata-Nunía, por la muerte de 4 bomberos, cuando trataban de apagar un incendio en el parque natural del sports, en el término municipal Tarraconense de Orta de San Joan. Otros dos permanecen ingresados en el hospital Valdebrón de Barcelona, en estado muy grave, con quemaduras de segundo y tercera grado en el 75 y el 50 por ciento de su cuerpo. Era en las 4 de la tarde cuando los bomberos se veían sorprendidos por un brusco cambió en la dirección del viento y quedaban atrapados entre las llamas, su trabajo consistía en evitar que el fuego llegará a zonas habitadas, la ministra de Defensa visiblemente afectada hablaba así de la tragedia. Durante toda la noche han trabajado en la zona 80 dotaciones de bomberos para estabilizar, el perímetro del incendio a un sin controlar. Cuéntana, además, desde hoy con la ayuda de 130 efectivos de la militar de emergencias, los últimos datos provisionales hablando de una superficie temada de 800 hectares de vegetación forestal, de las que 400 pertenecen al parque natural. El presidente de la Generalitat ha recibido las condolencias de los reyes de todos los partidos políticos y de distintas corporaciones municipales del país, las banderas de Cataluña donde anoy a mediasta.
transcript_en: in Cata-Nunía, for the death of 4 firefighters, when they were trying to put out a fire in the sports natural park, in the Tarragona municipality of Orta de San Joan. Two others remain admitted to the Valdebron hospital in Barcelona, ​​in very serious condition, with second and third degree burns on 75 and 50 percent of their bodies. It was at 4 in the afternoon when the firefighters were surprised by a sudden change in the direction of the wind and were trapped in the flames. Their job was to prevent the fire from reaching inhabited areas. The visibly affected Minister of Defense spoke in this way about the tragedy. title: SSRS Tutorials: Lesson 11 - Creating Graphs/Charts in SSRS 2008 R2
description: This demo gives you an overview on how to create basic graphs and charts using SSRS 2008 R2. This demo shows you ways to represent large volumes of data using visualization techniques.
transcript: Hello and welcome to this demo. So SSR is 2008, R2 provides us a lot of visualization tools. It provides us a lot of charts, graphs and if you look at the toolbox, you find a lot of other things like data bars, path lines and so on and so forth. So it basically allows us to represent huge volumes of data in visual manner like a chart or a pie chart or a graph or a kind of stuff. kind of stuff. Along with that you also see there is an option called as map. So it allows us to represent geographical data in the form of a map. We will take this in a separate tutorial where we discuss what our SREPIs and how to create layers in a map, how to embed data in a particular map and so on and so forth. In this tutorial what we are going to look as how to get some data set and then represent the data in the form of a graph or a chart or something like that. So what I'm going to do is I'm going to create a new report and the same new item and I'll call this as graphs. So what I'm going to do is I am going to create the same data set, which I created for my Microsoft. So we have some data to work with. All right, so we'll go to the graphs first of all via the connection string. Okay, and then I am going to create a new data set, make sure I remove the bad because I don't need any parameters over here. All right, so I have some data to work with. So, so far we have seen that we have dragged and dropped the table control, a matrix control and so on and so forth. But what we're going to do over here is we're going to drag and drop a chart control. So as soon as we do that, you see that you get a pop-up which I'll see you that which shape do you need. And then you see there are a lot of graphs for us. There are column charts, line charts, shades, bars, area and so on and so forth. I would really encourage you to explore more on this one, maybe try out different shapes. For this tutorial, let's take something very simple, like maybe the first one. So as soon as you click on OK, you see that there is kind of structure of the graph represented over here, and this is what we need to configure. Now just to give you a heads up everything over here is totally configurable like you could really change the title to have something like my first graph you could actually write an expression for this one you can totally control the legends totally control the colors you can make the colors dynamic and so on and so forth. So what we will do is let's go back to our report data and let's okay. So we are going to use the Content Region code in our x-axis and let's have the Let's see, let's see, let's see what makes sense over here, the series, let's have the year and in the totals, let's have total dew, let's see how this looks like, okay, We have some interesting graph, which basically shows you the control region code and for 2002, there is basically a legend created for you, the sales for us around 25 million or more than 25 million and so on and so forth, that's just a little bit bigger so that we can see more clearly, let's get preview, okay this looks somewhat nice, but again now Now, you would need this to be represented in a different format, so you could really have a currency representation of this one and then kind of, let's see, let's actually hit preview. But I would recommend you should be exploring the other tools also, the pie charts and stuff like that. But essentially, the concept remains the same, that you need to define three things. One is the exactest y-axis and what goes inside the graph. And RSSR takes care of the remaining things. So that's all about visualization and how to embed graphs and stuff into your reports. Thanks for watching.

title: Remady ft. Manu-L live No Superstar @ KV Fäscht Zürich 2011 (20 Jahre Jubiläum)
description: Remady ft. Manu-L live No Superstar @ KV Fäscht Zürich 2011 (20 Jahre Jubiläum)    Am 8. Oktober wird sich die KV Zürich Business School bereits zum 20. Mal in einen einzigartigen Tanzpalast verwandeln: ein Jubiläum eines Events, der im gleichen Jahr startete wie die Street Parade: 1992.  Eine einmalige Stimmung, die in dieser Form nur am KV-FÄSCHT herrscht, ein kostenloser Stylingcorner sowie eine sensationelle Light- und Laser-Show machen den Event zu einem der erfolgreichsten Party-Anlässe der Schweiz.    Headlinerin des Jubiläums-KV-FÄSCHT ist die 22-jährige rumänische House-Sängerin Alexandra Stan, bekannt durch ihren Riesenhit «Mr. Saxobeat». Kaum ein anderer Song wurde in den letzten Monaten so häufig in den Clubs und im Radio gespielt. An den Plattentellern sorgen Sir Colin, Mr. Da-Nos, Christopher S, M-Live & DJ Slice sowie die Live-Acts Remady feat. Manu-L und Mike Candys für tonnenweise gute Laune.

title: The politics of the public servant strike
description: In this video clip, the Electoral Institute for the Sustainability of Democracy in Africa's Ebrahim Fakir, speaks on the politics of the public service strike and its effect on the tripartite alliance.
hashtags: ebrahim fakir, public servant strike, EISA, Creamer Media, Politics, Polity
transcript: Welcome to Creamer Media's Palatee. I'm Amy Witheredon. With me in the studio, I have Abraham Fakir of the Electoral Institute for the Sustainability of Democracy in Africa to talk about strike action and the tripartite alliance. Welcome, Abraham. With the ongoing public-servered strike, dialier-fitting South Africans due to stoppages in hospitals and schools, the government has come across as toothless in its ability to control the strikers. Why are striking essential workers allowed to stay off work even after minister Richard Verloitte ordered them back to work? Well in the first instance I suspect essential services workers and men to be art and strike and they strike easing effect or not to be protected in terms of the label or because they use a essential services workers bargaining council to which they would take their would just dispute anything else. But I think this is part of a broader trend in which you have a state which appears to be becoming increasingly in more ineffective and it appears to be also seeding its authority. And so politically, the ANC, the Alliance still would appear from the 2009 election and I suspect the test will come again in the 2011 local government elections in elsewhere appeared to enjoy high levels of political legitimacy, but I think increasingly it is becoming clear that the governance credibility that the ANC government is enjoying as opposed to the ANC's political party or social movement, but the ANC as a government is enjoying less in less credibility and I think key sectors of the alliance, such as the workers, I infect them and straighten that this is the case and they central workers have actually I think by being as defined as they are, demonstrated the point even further, that the state is not only seated its authority, which I think is in fact quite a dangerous thing, where state does not enforce the rules that it in fact can and legitimately should. So it's seated its authority. Beyond just simply seeding its authority, the fallback for governance is that its ability to actually and force the rules that I established is becoming weaker and secondly that it's enforcement ability and the coercion which is required in that enforcement ability is also receiving. So this seems as message to a whole bunch of other sectors in society. Well, it appears that the rules are not consistently and predictably enforced. The state's ability to do so and therefore it's authority authority is receding and has preceded it in many instances and if these essential services workers could have done so in such open defiance, why wouldn't other sectors so it's not far off I would assume that corporates might decide well the rules on being enforced, the frameworks and the ability of the state to ensure this kind of oversight in enforcing the rules is not there so why should we and I think that's the danger, that's the danger of signal this is sending or this does send, with respect to two key areas of state performance in state capacity. And if the state can't enforce these, and at the same time it is those very people who constitute and make up the state who are in the street. It's literally telling us a story about the fact that the state is becoming increasingly more absent, and government is becoming increasingly more absent in the everyday life of South Africa. But surely it's simple enough to make an example and rest a few of these essential service trackers or have their lost all credibility. Well, I think that is possible, but I think that's something more subtle that's going on, and that subtlety is essentially quite clearly political. And I suspect what in the broad of view of some of the more conservative elements in the ANC are, is that they would, in fact, like to see Cossato being reduced to an economic union, to being a union, which is simply focused on shop floor issues, which is simply interested in wage negotiations, safety standards, work, enforcing work, rights, etc. Whereas, in fact, Cossato's tradition has been that of a social movement union, the union Federation which is genuinely and quite heavily interested and invested in a whole range of broader sociopolitical and economic issues beyond simply issues of immediate concern to their workers. And I think they would like to narrow, there are some conservator plays in the ANZ, would like to narrow society's focus so that it relaxes the kind of oversight tension that Cossato is, in fact, in their lines, exercising over the ANC. Even though this particular strike is about public sector employees, they're asking for wages, higher wages, and better conditions of employment. And that is clearly a shop floor issue. It is clearly linked to issues of community concern. Because the workers see themselves and Cossato, of course, see themselves. ourselves, firstly, as members of the community, before simply being workers. So the two are inexplicably linked. Conservative elements in the ANC would like to see that split, would like to see that rendered a sander, would like to see Kusar to be reduced to some kind of a conemistic unit. And I think here what the strategy that may be at play is not to alienate many of the public sector workers too far, so that somewhere down the line, they can actually get the public sector workers organized in ways outside of Kusar to. And then it would leave Kosa to the Union Federation to organize workers which are largely located in the private sector either in the mines and in other industry which is not owned by government in which government doesn't have control and government is not the employer. And what we did then try and do is set up this grand divide as it happened in Sambia and in Zimbabwe between what the ruling party would set up as the liberators as opposed to these narrow workers who are in fact becoming conduits for outside agendas and outside interests and are being counter-evolutionary. And these words are being banded about all over. And so I think it is in the long term, or at least in the medium term, to set up this divide between members of their lines to push closer to out their lines, but to keep the public sector workers in. So it set up this bull walk in this clash between the two. And that, of course, I think will simply become a rules. And it's a rules to the extent that those who are using the state as a side of accumulation for their own private interests, collusion with other private sector actors to continue using. And the state's becoming You know, almost a rentiest state-way, predatory interests have taken root and simply use it to continue their own accumulation path. And use liberation, use independence, use national sovereignty, use nationalism itself, as a mask for this kind of recidivist behavior. And I suspect that what may in fact be going on as a strategy. It may not, you know, it may be entirely misleading in the situation, That's what I suspect in the medium term is, is strategy that lies behind this. So, getting back to the alliance, many analysts think that government will give into labour demands for 8.6% increase due to the track record in submitting to labour. What does this mean for the politics of the tripartar alliance? Well, I'm not of the view that government is always submitted to labour. I think labour has always shown that in the balance of forces between different constituents of the alliance that, in previous rounds of the negotiations, even though government held out for so long, the balance of power did lie, what the people on the streets, what the workers on the streets, who in many cases had legitimate grievances, legitimate demands and I suspect, is through in this case too. So, I'm not sure, I don't agree, I don't agree with the fact that government is always given into labor's demands, they have of course met some of them over the last five six years in this success of negotiations, but this time I think that they have sent the signal that they both sides have sent the signal that they were willing to wait this out. Do it equally. Look, eventually one of them is going to relent and I suspect it is going to be government because it's simply cannot afford to let the situation continue unabated. But there in is I think it's striking of the bargain with some of public sector workers and especially the essential workers, the essential workers, by suggesting, look, you were out in strike and you weren't sanctioned, you weren't disciplined, you weren't fired and you weren't arrested either. So it's bolding a degree of sympathy, political legitimacy, some kind of credibility, so that there's some compatibility between ruling section in government and these workers. And that I suspect will set up this huge clash that I was talking about. So the politics of the Alliance are squarely mired in the entire strike in the dynamics of the strike, but the dynamics are changing and changing fast. It is no longer a simple case of it's Cossato as a union, as a constituent of the Alliance, simply going against a sector of the agency. This entire strike, I think, has been broadly enmeshed within the agency's own succession, within their own succession debates around 2012 and about the upcoming National General Council at the end of September. And I think this is a show of force by some constituents of their alliance, about wanting to be a harmonic when the National General Council comes up because they would want to be dominant in certain policy positions They would want, and you can use just two as an example. The media appeals tribunal and the whole debate about nationalization. So the strike is I think being used for multiple reasons. They are genuine wage concerns, they are genuine worker concerns, they are genuine negotiations going on, but it is also a show of force, it is also an attempt for one ideological section of the alliance and itself is splintered with itself is splintered so it is some sections of Kusatur which are driving part of the strike of course they are unified on the wage demands on the negotiations of government but they are far from unified on taking positions on certain policy issues and I think that this is an attempt to show force both within Kusatur itself and its constituents as well as between Cossato and other elements of their alliance. So the strike I think is being used for multiple purposes and multiple reasons. And it's fracturing, I think, the alliance further than it ever has been. It's reached a stage where there is now open calls that the state has become predatory, that certain leaders are not just not credible, but also illegitimate. and this has happened on both sides, so it's very interesting and I think this has split the alliance further or at least caused divisions in the alliance further and more tense than there ever has been since 1994. Thank you, Abraham. That was Abraham Fakir of the Electoral Institute for the Sustainability of Democracy in Africa.

It is no longer a simple case of it's Cossato as a union, as a constituent of the Alliance, simply going against a sector of the agency. This entire strike, I think, has been broadly enmeshed within the agency's own succession, within their own succession debates around 2012 and about the upcoming National General Council at the end of September. And I think this is a show of force by some constituents of their alliance, about wanting to be a harmonic when the National General Council comes up because they would want to be dominant in certain policy positions They would want, and you can use just two as an example. The media appeals tribunal and the whole debate about nationalization. So the strike is I think being used for multiple reasons. They are genuine wage concerns, they are genuine worker concerns, they are genuine negotiations going on, but it is also a show of force, it is also an attempt for one ideological section of the alliance and itself is splintered with itself is splintered so it is some sections of Kusatur which are driving part of the strike of course they are unified on the wage demands on the negotiations of government but they are far from unified on taking positions on certain policy issues and I think that this is an attempt to show force both within Kusatur itself and its constituents as well as between Cossato and other elements of their alliance. So the strike I think is being used for multiple purposes and multiple reasons. And it's fracturing, I think, the alliance further than it ever has been. It's reached a stage where there is now open calls that the state has become predatory, that certain leaders are not just not credible, but also illegitimate. and this has happened on both sides, so it's very interesting and I think this has split the alliance further or at least caused divisions in the alliance further and more tense than there ever has been since 1994. Thank you, Abraham. That was Abraham Fakir of the Electoral Institute for the Sustainability of Democracy in Africa..

title: BBB12 Mona tem crise e detona Jonas: 'Só tem beleza' ( imagens )
description: BBB12 Mona tem crise e detona Jonas: 'Só tem beleza' ( imagens ) Ainda chorando muito, Monique desabafa com João Carvalho: -O que o Mister faz? Cuida da imagem. Bonito, bonito sempre-, referindo-se a Jonas, e continua: -É que nem o Yuri falava: beleza não se leva para lugar nenhum. E ele só tem beleza para levar, porque só quer cuidar da imagem dele e do que ele fala-.  A gaúcha não poupa críticas ao modelo: -Uma pessoa que é um robô, que cuida do que pensa, do que fala, do que respira, eu não quero que ganhe. Eu não vou ganhar porque eu sou desse jeito. E nem quero ganhar um milhão, quero correr atrás de um milhão-.  João Carvalho segue ouvindo as reclamações de Monique em silêncio. -Cansei de brincar de boneca, eu só estou ficando com ele porque a Renata foi embora. Aí, não posso falar sobre o Fael, não sei o quê, o fulano não sei o que mais...-, aponta a gaúcha. O mineiro tenta opinar, mas logo Jonas chega na sala e quer saber o que Monique estava falando sobre ele. A estudante de Administração dispara: -Tô falando de ti sim... Que você só se preocupa com tudo o que você fala, tudo o que você acha, tudo o que você pensa, tudo de tudo... Eu vou sair porque não penso em nada. Eu sou essa com uma maquiagem borrada, com os peitos pra fora, de calcinha e eu não tô nem aí-.  Mostrando-se surpreso, Jonas pergunta: -Você acha que eu sou assim? Então tá, prazer em te conhecer então, tá?-, ironiza o modelo, estendendo a mão para Monique.  A sister continua a bombardeá-lo: -Você sempre me trata como um nada, como uma porcaria, como um travesseiro qualquer que você dorme de noite. Que carinho você me faz, cara?-, e continua: -Eu tô brincando com Fael e com a Noemí, os dois levaram na brincadeira e você não levou-.  O modelo conta que também brincou com Fael e protesta: -Eu disse: meu amigo é um cabrón. Você acha que eu vou falar sério um negócio desses? Acha que não foi brincadeira? Agora você fala um monte de coisas... Você precisa fazer esse show para denegrir a minha imagem?-.  Monique segue reclamando sobre as atitudes do brother e a discussão não para. Minutos depois, Jonas desiste de argumentar e deixa a gaúcha falando sozinha na sala.

title: the.LIFE Files TV: From Jerusalem To New Jersey
description: In this installment of the.LIFE Files TV we catch up with Shyne in the holy land Jerusalem where he currently resides. Shyne can be seen walking through the streets of Jerusalem where he does a few impromptu freestyles for his fans as well as going to the club and discussing the bible with elder Rabbis. Po gets deep in this exclusive clip and talks about his inevitable return to the United States.  We then head over to Englewood, NJ to catch up with Dorian Grace, owner of Dlux NJ - an upscale clothing boutique. Dorian gives us a tour of her space and shows us some of her new pieces you may have seen on the likes of Nicole Richie and Rihanna - while talking about her inspiration for fashion, working with model India (Charli Baltimore's daughter) for her look book and being an entrepreneur.

title: Home for Sale - Lila Delman Real Estate - Scarbourgh House
description: "Scarbourgh House", an iconic piece of Rhode Island history situated on Ocean Road in Narragansett. With spectacular ocean views and easy access to white sandy beaches, this desirable 1927 Arts and Crafts style home retains the best of its classic style while offering the comforts of modern living.  The beautifully landscaped, oversized lot is announced by a gate and handsomely crafted, lighted, stone pillars complimenting the home's architectural lines. The property's privacy and estate-like ambiance is further enhanced by the wooded acres adjacent Fort Greene. The grounds feature a detached cottage-style garage, an enclosed outdoor shower, and an ocean-facing brick herringbone terrace.  Enjoy ocean breezes and the sound of crashing waves throughout "Scarbourgh House". This lovely home offers includes three comfortable bedrooms, two updated full baths, a bright kitchen with a vintage pantry, original fir wood floors, and an ample screened porch ideal for both lounging and dining. The spacious living room includes original architectural details, ocean views, and an oversized brick fireplace. The large lot allows for expansion, if desired.  Lovingly renovated, amenities include central air conditioning, a new heating system, granite countertops, stainless steel appliances and updated baths. Renovations include the conveniences of natural gas, town sewers, and town water.    Enjoy the best of coastal living from this "one of a kind" offering just steps from a pristine ocean beach. Affectionately known by locals as simply "Scarborough", this beach is nearly one half mile long. Conveniently located just 35 miles south of Providence, 90 minutes from Logan International Airport in Boston and 3 hours from Manhattan, this special place draws many visitors year after year. The spectacular location and numerous amenities allows "Scarborough House" to be a perfect year-round home, vacation get-away or investment property.  Contact: Tom Denniston 401-284-4822 tom.denniston@liladelman.com
